      Sports Goal, Make the Most of Every Workout

      • 50 Sports Modes with GPS Enabled: Swimming, Yoga, Running, Cycling, Golf, Diving, Camping & Hiking,Treadmill,Walking,Cricket, Baseball, Basketball, Table tennis, Badminton, Free training, Fishing..etc
      • Proper Sports Reminder: The watch will vibrate to remind you when your Stress or Blood oxygen exceed the normal value when you are outdoors or exercising intensely
      • Targted Sports Data Analysis: According to the WHO health promotion, more targeted optimization of your muscle building and calorie consumption
      • Sports Self-recognition: No action is required before exercising, just start running or swimming,enter "Auto Sport Mode" automatically

      Fitness Watch, Built for Better Fitness Results

      • Activity: Refer to how many daily calories you've burned. Keeping certain amount of calories can help improve your physical health
      • Steps: Count steps for all activities that generate steps, such as walking, running, going up and down stairs and even doing housework
      • Calorie: Calorie consumption, are composed of activity calories, all-day calories and food thermal efficiency
      • Distance: Refer to how far you move and walk throughout the day

      Advanced Health Tracker, Know Your Health Better

      Heart Rate Monitor: 24h continuous heart rate monitoring

      Blood Oxygen Monitor: Under your control, avoid excessive exercise

      Blood Pressure Monitor: Record real-time data and relax in time

      Stress Monitor: Know your Stress and Health better

      Sleep Monitor: Score Analyze sleep quality, give professional advice

      Menstural Cycle Care: track menstrual time and predict ovulation

      How customer reviews and ratings work

      Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

      To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

        I was really excited when I ordered this watch, and still use it daily. The ones that do work have been a game changer for me though, which is why I still gave this watch four stars.

        What I like about it:
        - It tracks steps pretty accurately
        - It tracks distance pretty accurately and also has the option to choose between miles or kilometers.
        - It also tracks calories burnt. I'm not sure how accurate it is, but it's good to get a general idea...
        - It tracks heart beat and blood oxygen
        - It tracks different sleep stages time, total sleep time, light sleep time and deep sleep time.
        - When the wrist is raised to look at the watch it's face automatically lights up.
        - It easy to charge and holds the battery charge for several days. How many depends on usage.
        - This one can get annoying, but I desperately needed it! I alerts you when you've been sitting > 30 mins.
        - It is waterproof! Can be worn while swimming
        - Offers settings for 25 different sports. I only used the walking setting and it seemed accurate..
        - When/if connected it can find the phone/watch and makes it beep.
        - It includes a small and a large wrist band.

        It also has other features, alarm, weather, nd the face of the watch can be personalized with one of their options or one of your own.

        I heard that there is a way to also send text messages via voice, but I have not been able to figure it out.

        Why I only gave it 4 stars instead of 5.
        - It tracks blood pressure, but at least in my case, it is not accurate.

Battery life is alright and it is comfortable enough to wear. However, I find that most of the health data is just not realistic, I get the same blood pressure readings whether I am wearing the watch or not, so cannot recommend if you need this for fitness and health data.

        5.0 out of 5 stars Amazing battery life, good functionality
        Reviewed in the United Kingdom on September 19, 2023
        Amazon Vine Customer Review of Free Product( What's this? )
        This is a really good smart watch for those on a budget, it allows for calls, shows you messages and notifications from various apps and gives a good look at basic health statistics such as HR, SpO2, sleep tracking etc. It also has a blood pressure reading but I dont know how it calculates this and this how accurate it is.

        The battery life of this watch is by far the longest of any smartwatch Ive used in the past. I can get at least a week out of this with regular checking and raise to wake turned on. Without raise to wake, battery life is considerably longer.

        All in all its a great smart watch with some decent features and looks quite good. With the slim strap its less irritating to people who arent used to wearing watches.

        Charger is the same as a lot of budget smart watches so shouldnt be too difficult to replace if lost.

        Well deserved 5/5.
